So I went to Kael Drakkel from the Wakening Lands and did some scouting. The giants -as well as being ugly abominations- are stupid and predictable. They think they have a formidable guard on their perimeter in their city. They're wrong. I sat down and hid right at the edge. (That was funny, hiding in plain sight -stupid oafs. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    ) Anyhow, I took some notes on the guard rotation.<br>
Watch Sgt. Hyren (mob A below), Adjutant Rogrek (mob B), and a silly little dire wolf (mob C) are stationary about 1-200 yds in from where the stone appears to turn to ice. (Guessing on the distance.) A frost Giant Berserker (mob D) and his partner of the same name (mob E) come past (A,B,C) and stand in two spots for 54 seconds. D comes right to the stone, far enough away from E and A,B,C that apparently they don't notice an attack. E's patrol puts him far enough from A,B,C so they won't help him if attacked, but in between them and D's patrol. After D and E stand for 54 seconds at their posts, they wander behind A,B,C for 1:42 till their return.<br>
&lt;A,B,C,D,E cons to 51. A=light blue, B=light blue, C=green, D=low dark blue, E=light blue.&gt;&lt;edit&gt;A,B,C come alone.<br>
One other oaf wanders to the edge of the ice. A Lt. Coldforge. Every 4:40 he wanders up to the edge and barks commands, whether any of his troops are there or not. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     He then turns around and wanders I don't know where.<br>
<br>
&lt;ooc on&gt;This IMHO would make a great xp camp. Group needed. High 40's-low 50's tank. Cleric. Monk or chanter 40's up. Support healer for Lt. fight. He's 47 according to Alla's. Leaves two spots to be filled with classes that can get xp. Nuker should fill one of those slots. The hp's on giants are pretty large. I darn near kited a berserker to death. Gave up after he beat me to running hp's right before I could get him to that point &lt;edit&gt;berserkers, being berserk, don't run. They'll be easy. Lt. has been known to drop quest armor very rarely, but this is an xp camp. The only thing I couldn't figure out was spawn time, because I couldn't get that bastage to run before he made me run. I imagine those 6 mobs plus medding downtime would keep us busy, at least for a true xp group. (Mainly low-mid 40's. A high 40's group could probably handle more than those 6. Again, depends on spawn timer.&lt;edit&gt;estimated at 30 min.) I'll be available midnite PST, Wed. and Thur. night this week if we can throw a group together to try it. Otherwise, I'd like to get a group for 4pm PST Friday. I want to try it out, get a spawn timer and get a good idea of actual strength.&lt;ooc off&gt;<br>
<br>
Do I have any volunteers? Please let me know. &lt;First 6 to sign up filling the roles will go Friday. Cap is 51 or 52. Not sure if they turn green at 52 or not. Anyone after the first 6 will be considered reserve for the Friday group, so if you see those roles filled, sign up anyway. If this goes well, we'll do it weekly.&gt;<br>
<br>
&lt;edit&gt;Although this is designed for an xp group (see Death Squad as well) it's also an easy way to get CoV faction if you just wanna hang out at any level. Friday groups will go for 2 hours, then banking and NK for language class.<br>
